9:
Stop! If this goes any further, you
could get—
14:
You think you've won, have you?

Fools. The fight up until now was no
more than a dance.
17:
But now my preparations are
complete!
21:
When I am done with you, your
ashes will be left to—
27:
There is only one mage in this
kingdom that can conduct fire
through her blood... You are Shakari,
are you not?
34:
I am Light! Your champion! I have
returned!
39:
You mean to say that this pitiful
creature, which even now perches
trembling atop the head of a girl...
HE is our champion? You are surely
joking.
43:
The Lord of Shadow changed my
form into that of a beast. But within, I—
46:
I waited... for many long years.
Joshua too... He never stopped
believing. And to think that this
FARCE is what we laid all our hopes
on, I...
50:
We were born in the same village!
Your mother—
56: I DON'T WANT TO HEAR IT!
61:
...Tell me, Shakari. What has
happened to Excelion?
63:
How fares the King... and Princess
Lily? Why have things come to such
a turn?
68:
The champion Light vanished fifty
years ago.
71:
And now, a little beast appears,
which has assumed his name.
73:
And what's more, this beast is a pet
of death herself.

...Never has a jest been in poorer
taste.
77:
Please, you have to believe us! Light
IS a champion. And Stella—
80:
I know her name, boy. Stella,
Harbinger of Death. Destroyer of my
people.
85: ...I am Stella. But I am not a murderer.
88:
Come with me. Lilith shall determine
how you are served.
98:
The King, too, fell with the capital. All
that remains of the royal bloodline is
Lilith—Princess Lily's granddaughter.
101:
Joshua is also gone. He died waiting
for a champion that never came.
103:
Now come. Make any attempt at
escape, and I will kill you.
116:
Hehehe... The Witch of Burning Blood
and the Champion Light...

But how curious...
118: Stella... You shouldn't be here at all.
